===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈbæn.dən/}}
* {{audio|en-us-abandon.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Etymology 1===
* First attested in 1390.
* From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|abandounen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|abandoner|lang=fro}}, formed from {{term|a|lang=fro}} + {{term|bandon||jurisdiction, control|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|ML.}} {{term|bannum||proclamation|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|frk}} ''*ban'', from {{proto|Germanic|bannanan|to proclaim, command|lang=en}} (compare {{etyl|en|-}} {{term|ban|lang=en}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|bʰeh₂-||bʰa-|to speak|lang=en}}.
* Displaced {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|forleten||to abandon|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|forlætan|forlǣtan|lang=ang}}, {{term|anforlætan|anforlǣtan|lang=ang}}) and {{etyl|enm|-}} {{term|forleven||to leave behind, abandon|lang=enm}} (from {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|forlæfan|forlǣfan|lang=ang}}).

====Verb====
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To [[give up]] control of, to [[surrender]], as in a ship or a position, typically in response to overwhelming odds or impending dangers.
# {{transitive}} To leave behind; to [[desert]]; to [[forsake]], in spite of a duty or responsibility.
#* {{rfdate}} I. Taylor:
#*: Hope was overthrown, yet could not be '''abandoned'''.
#: ''Many baby girls have been '''abandoned''' on the streets of Beijing every day.''
# {{transitive|obsolete}} To [[cast out|cast]] or [[drive out]]; to [[banish]]; to [[expel]]; to [[reject]].
#* '''1594''', [[w:William Shakespeare|William Shakespeare]], ''The Taming of the Shrew'', act I, scene ii:
#*: Being all this time '''abandoned''' from your bed.
# {{transitive}} To no longer [[exercise]] a [[right]], [[title]], or [[interest]], especially with no interest of reclaiming it again; to [[yield]]; to [[relinquish]].
# {{transitive}} To give oneself over, or to [[yield]] without restraint or control.
# {{transitive}} To turn away from; to permit to lapse; to desist in doing, practicing, following, or adhering to.
# {{transitive}} To surrender to the [[insurer]] the item that was insured, so as to claim payment for a [[total loss]].

